Wash and dry all produce. Bring a #large pot{} of salted water to a boil. Trim and discard bottom 2 inches from @asparagus{16%ounce} stalks. Halve @heirloom grape tomatoes{8%ounce}. Cut @Gouda cheese{4%slice} into small pieces. Finely mince @chives{1/4%ounce}. Halve @lemon{1}; cut one half into wedges.

Once water boils, add @lobster ravioli{18%ounce} to pot. Lower heat and reduce to a gentle simmer. Cook until just shy of al dente, ~{2-4%minutes}. Remove from heat (do not drain). Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{2%teaspoon} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Stir @butter{2%tablespoon}(plain) and @Tuscan heat spice{1%tablespoon}.

Add @flour{2%tablespoon} to pan and cook, stirring, until it loses its raw smell, about ~{2%minutes}. Slowly pour in @milk{13.5%ounce} while stirring with your other hand. Stir in @veggie stock concentrate{1} and bring to a simmer. Let bubble, stirring occasionally, until mixture starts to thicken, ~{3-5%minutes}. Reduce heat to low. Add @Italian cheese blend{1%cup} and Gouda cheeses, stirring to melt.

Stir 1/4 cup pasta water into sauce in pan. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. > TIP: If sauce is very thick, stir in a little more pasta water. Remove pan from heat. Heat broiler to medium high. Spread 1/3 of the sauce on the bottom of a #9-by-13-inch baking dish{}. Scatter half the tomatoes inside dish. Gently drain ravioli, then arrange in dish in an even layer. Pour over remaining sauce and scatter remaining tomatoes over.

Mix @panko breadcrumbs{1%cup} and @Parmesan cheese{1%cup} in a #small bowl{}, then sprinkle evenly over ravioli in dish. Place dish under broiler. Broil until toasted, about ~{3%minutes}. > TIP: Keep an eye out for any burning. Set aside and let rest ~{5%minutes}. Heat a drizzle of olive oil in another large pan over medium-high heat. Add asparagus and cook, tossing, until tender, about ~{5%minutes}. Add @garlic herb butter{2%tablespoon} and toss.

Squeeze juice from lemon half over asparagus. Season with salt and pepper. Cut ravioli bake into squares and add to plates. Sprinkle with chives. Add asparagus to the side; pour any butter in pan over. Sprinkle with @?chili flakes{1%teaspoon} to taste. Serve with lemon wedges.